The paper deals with optimization problems related to directed graphs, which suggests that it could belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. The use of dichotomy classifications and computational complexity analysis suggests that it could also belong to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) category. The study of homomorphisms and optimization problems in graphs suggests that it could belong to the Graph Theory (cs.GT) category. Finally, the real-world motivation for the problem and the use of optimization techniques suggest that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category.
